13/03/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The Hague tribunal's chief prosecutor, Carla del Ponte, has accepted an invitation to visit Croatia, according to a statement released by Zagreb on Thursday (13 March).
She sent a letter to Deputy Prime Minister Goran Granic confirming her intentions for "immediate contacts" with Croatian authorities to discuss open issues and improve co-operation.
Officials expect her in mid to late April.
(HINA - 13/03/03)
